posts.title: NY State Emergency Rental Assistance Program and Housing Resources
posts.text: Watch a recording of a presentation we hosted about the Emergency Rental Assistance Program with Jordan Dewbre of Bronxworks as well as find links to many other related resources.

posts.title: "World Refugee Day: Welcoming and Learning Together" Discussion Recap & Book Lists
posts.text: Listen to a conversation with panelists from NYC organizations who work with refugees to further understand different immigration stories and experiences, and learn about the ways that everyone can support this work.

posts.title: Celebrate Immigrant Heritage Week 2021 & NYPL's World Literature Festival
posts.text: NYPL's World Literature Festival, taking place April 12–30, 2021, celebrates books and writers from around the world and reflects the languages spoken in our communities. It also coincides with NYC's Immigrant Heritage Week (April 12–18). We invite you to join the Library through the end of the month and beyond to discover our multilingual resources, what our patrons are reading in different languages, free online events, book recommendations, and more.

posts.title: A Multilingual Recommendation Book List for Welcoming Week
posts.text: We're sharing staff favorites in Spanish, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, French, Russian, Polish, Arabic, and Italian.

posts.title: A Taste of Korean Programs & Collections
posts.text: Join us for online book discussions and more.

posts.title: 한국어 프로그램 & 한국책 맛집
posts.text: 아이들에게 한국어로 동화책을 읽어주고 싶으신가요? 한국책을 좋아하고 함께 얘기해 볼 장소가 필요하신가요? 그렇다면 이곳으로 오세요!

posts.title: Courage, Strength, & Determination: E-Books to Honor World Refugee Day
posts.text: Told by different voices from different places; these stories are important reads throughout the year.

posts.title: Celebrating the Immigrant Experience with Books for Children and Teens
posts.text: Stories through the eyes, emotions, and experiences of young people.

posts.title: Resources for Immigrants in NYC
posts.text: Our librarians have compiled a selection of the many resources available for immigrants in New York City.

posts.title: Hispanic Heritage Month: Recommending Latin American Women Authors
posts.text: Often overshadowed by their male counterparts, these Latina writers have created some of the world's great Latin American-based writing. Meet them and their work with our latest recommendation list.

posts.title: Citizenship Day / Constitution Day: Supporting Your Citizenship Journey
posts.text: The New York Public Library provides resources, programs, and services that support those New Yorkers seeking to become American citizens.

posts.title: Health Insurance Open Enrollment 2017: Assistance at The New York Public Library
posts.text: Do you need to apply for health insurance? Do you have questions about health insurance? We can help.

posts.title: Exploring Citizenship Day: Programs, Books & Films
posts.text: Constitution Day and Citizenship Day is observed each year on September 17 to commemorate the signing of the Constitution on September 17, 1787, and to “recognize all who, by coming of age or by naturalization, have become citizens.”

posts.title: National Book Lovers Day - What is your favorite book?
posts.text: What happens when an impromptu question is sent to NYPL staff in honor of August 9th “National Book Lovers Day”? It becomes a great conversation starter with amazing recommendations.

posts.title: Celebrando el mes de la Herencia Hispana: Biografías
posts.text: En honor del "mes de la Herencia Hispana", presentamos a continuación una selección de biografías recientes que esperamos sea de su agrado.

posts.title: ¡Celebre el mes de inscripción para tarjetas de la biblioteca con NYPL!
posts.text: Septiembre es el Mes de inscripción para tarjetas de la biblioteca.

posts.title: Elecciones 2016: Regístrese, Investigue y Vote
posts.text: Las Convenciones Nacionales Demócrata y Republicana han finalizado, y las nominaciones presidenciales de los dos principales partidos políticos de los Estados Unidos son oficiales: Hillary Clinton por el Partido Demócrata y Donald Trump por el Partido Republicano. Con las elecciones generales a sólo cien días, aquí le presentamos recursos para ayudarle a prepararse para votar.

posts.title: Free Citizenship Resources
Lectura de verano: "Entra en el juego ¡Lee!"
posts.text: Este año la lectura de verano se enfoca en motivar a los niños a leer y a usar los recursos y programas ofrecidos en las bibliotecas.

posts.title: Desfile Puertorriqueño | Puerto Rican Day Parade
posts.text: Every year on the eve of the second Sunday of the month of June New York City holds the National Puerto Rican day parade. This is a celebration that takes over the entire city, fills it with beautiful events, festivals that display the beauty of the Puerto Rican culture.

posts.title: Celebrating Immigrant Heritage Month 2016
posts.text: Happy Immigrant Heritage Month! The Library is proud to be hosting a wide array of events throughout the month of June to celebrate.

posts.title: Día de los caídos en guerra / Memorial Day
posts.text: Con frecuencia la gente relaciona el “Memorial Day” con un fin de semana largo a fines del mes de mayo: no hay clases en las escuelas, se abren las piscinas y las playas, y comienza  extraoficialmente el verano. Pero exactamente que es Memorial Day? - El Día de Conmemoración a los Caídos.

posts.text: A selection of children's books on the refugee experience.

posts.title: National Hispanic Heritage Month, Selections
posts.text: In honor of Hispanic Heritage Month we will showcase a selection of readings from our collections, chosen by NYPL staff.

posts.title: Films to Celebrate Immigrant Heritage Month
posts.text: Recent films that portray the American Immigrant Experience. From documentaries to wonderful works of fiction, they all provide some insight in what builds our diverse nation.

posts.title: Find Winners of the 2014 Goodreads Choice Awards at the Library
posts.text: The books listed below were chosen as winners of the 2014 Goodreads Choice Awards, "the major book award decided by readers." There is something for everyone! Children, teens, and adults.

posts.title: The Wonderful Wide World of Sesame Street
posts.text: Did you know that Sesame Street has international reach? Sesame Workshop, the company that produces Sesame Street, also co-produces international versions of the beloved television show in many different languages for audiences in many different countries.
